      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the slow-moving principal on your student loan is a common feeling, but it's all part of the loan's magic. When you make your full payments, you're actually paying both the principal and the interest. The interest is calculated based on the remaining balance, which means it starts off small but grows over time. This is why it feels like the principal isn't moving much at first. It's like a slow-moving river that seems to barely flow at the beginning, but it gains momentum as it goes along. Keep making those full payments, and you'll see the principal eventually start to decrease faster. Just remember, it's a bit like trying to fill a hole with a spoon - it takes time, but it will eventually get filled.",
